<h4>Companies Who Can Help</h4>
<p>
	There  are many service companies that bring OpenStack expertise to the table such as B1 Systems, Cloudscaling, CloudTP, Grid Dynamics, Mirantis and Rackspace Cloud Builders. If you are looking for someone to guide you through these choices, help you execute your cloud strategy and provide support, this is a great place to start.  Several of these companies such as Mirantis and Rackspace Cloud Builders also provide OpenStack training courses for cloud administrators.
</p>
<hr/>
<h4>OpenStack Tools</h4>
<div class="span-16">
	<p>
		Once you have your OpenStack cloud up and running, you'll want to explore the many tools available to help you manage it.  These are tools that talk to the OpenStack API and can be found by looking for the "Built for OpenStack" logo.  Popular tools for managing OpenStack clouds include Enstratus, New Relic, Scalr and Zenoss.
	</p>
</div>
